column5: Already thinking about fall fishing and hunting plans. Any-one (i suspect one member may, who seems to be the Temagami expert) know of, or could pin point Alice Lake in relationship to Rabbit Lake? thanks
Update, I just found it thanks to the link that Irishfield sent out on Crown land atlas. thanks
You take the Rabbit Lake Road.. Turn Right just North of "Gramps" Bait and Tackle.... that is across the road from Angus Lake.
thanks, if we go in the fall, what should the target fish be? can walleye or pike be found on it?
Haven't fished it.. but the only thing the old lakes of Temagami map shows in it are Brook Trout.
I've spent quite a bit of time around the rabbit lake area.  I 'm not sure about Alice lake, but I know most of the small lakes around there have good size pike in them, some also have walleye.
I may just try to get ya to scratch your head a bit about it......first i have to confirm we are going. thanks
